Sadio Mane has sent a message to Mohamed Salah and Naby Keita as the Liverpool trio get set to play in The Africa Cup of Nations. The tournament begins today and the Senegalese international has revealed his ‘special message’ for his Liverpool team-mates. In the video, a confident Mane cheekily suggests Senegal will reach the final and goes on to express his regret that he cannot play both Salah’s Egypt and Keita’s Guinea in the showpiece. Antoine Griezmann Wants Atletico Madrid Stay Arsenal Not Good Enough, Must Apologise – Arteta Mane said: “I have special message to my to friends, which is this, Naby Keita and Mo Salah, unfortunately I cannot play against two teams in the final so I have to play one. I want to say good luck to all of you, take care guys” Mane’s Senegal get started in the tournament tomorrow against Zimbabwe while Naby Keita will also represent Guinea on the same day against Malawi. Mohamed Salah will begin his campaign on Tuesday when he is expected to turn out for Egypt against Nigeria.